Photo by Dr. Sheetal on May 19, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'Mistake #1: Over-cleansing Your YourSkin Skin What you're doing: Washing your face 3-4 times a day thinking it will reduce oil and acne. Why it's wrong: Overcleansing strips away natural natural oils, disrupts your barrier, and triggers more sebum production. Derm Tip: Cleanse only twice daily with a gentle cleanser according to your skin type.'.

Photo by Dr. Sheetal on May 19, 2025. May be an image of ointment and text that says 'Mistake #2: Skipping Sunscreen Indoors and on cloudy days. What you're doing: Applying sunscreen only when it's sunny. Why it's wrong: UV rays penetrate windows, and blue light from screens can worsen pigmentation and aging. Derm Tip: Use a broad-spectrum minimum SPF 30+ daily, even indoors. Reapply every 2-3 hours if you're near a window or on screens.'.

Photo by Dr. Sheetal on May 19, 2025. May be an image of ointment and text that says 'Mistake #3: Using Too Many Actives Together What you're doing: Layering vitamin C, retinol, AHAs, BHAs all in one routine. Why it's wrong: Can cause irritation, redness, peeling, and actually damage your skin barrier. Derm Tip: Introduce actives slowly. Alternate nights. Consult a dermatologist for a safe, effective routine.'.

Photo by Dr. Sheetal on May 19, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'Mistake #4: Trusting DIY Skincare Hacks What you're doing: Applying lemon juice, toothpaste, or baking soda on pimples or dark spots. Why it's wrong: These can cause burns, irritation, and long-term pigmentation. Derm Tip: Stick to evidence-based treatments. There's a reason dermatology is a science!'.

Photo by Dr. Sheetal on May 19, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'Mistake #5: Ignoring Your Neck & Hands What you're doing: Focusing skincare only on your face. Why it's wrong: Neck and hands show signs of aging first! Derm Tip: Extend your skincare (especially SPF & moisturizer) to neck and hands daily.'.
